This Homework Project works with dataframes in the package nycflights13 about flights, specifically a sample of domestic flights that departed from the three major New York City airports in 2013.

1 Data overview

1.1 Package loading

1.2 Package overview

  • The data package nycflights13 package contains five tabular data frames. In total there is information about:
    • 16 airlines
    • 1458 airports
    • 3322 planes
    • 336776 flights

The core dataframe flights has the following variables:

year, month, day: Date of departure.
dep_time, arr_time: Actual departure and arrival times (format HHMM or HMM), local time zone.
sched_dep_time, sched_arr_time: Scheduled departure and arrival times (format HHMM or HMM), local time zone.
dep_delay, arr_delay: Departure and arrival delays, in minutes. Negative times represent early departures/arrivals.
carrier: Two letter carrier abbreviation. See airlines-dataframe to get the full name.

flight: airlineâs flight number.
tailnum: planeâs tail number (unique aircraft ID).
origin, dest: three-letter airport codes for departure and arrival; full names/locations are in airports.
air_time: minutes spent in the air.
distance: distance flown in miles.
hour, minute: scheduled departure hour and minute.
time_hour: scheduled departure time rounded to the hour (date-time), useful for joining with weather.

# Data Wrangling

```{.r .cell-code}
flights |>
  filter(!is.na(air_time), air_time > 0) |>               
  mutate(                                                  
    speed_kmh = (distance * 1.609344) / (air_time / 60)   
  ) |>
  select(air_time, distance, speed_kmh) |>
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = speed_kmh)) +                   
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 50) +                          
  labs(
    title = "Flight speeds (km/h)",
    x = "Speed (km/h)",
    y = "Number of flights"
  )

  arrange(desc(avg_arr_delay))

library(dplyr)

:::

# Create distance categories
flights2 <- nycflights13::flights |>
  mutate(
    distance_group = case_when(
      distance < 500 ~ "Short (<500 miles)",
      distance >= 500 & distance < 1500 ~ "Medium (500â1500 miles)",
      distance >= 1500 ~ "Long (1500+ miles)"
    )
  )
# Average arrival delay by distance group
avg_delay <- flights2 |>
  group_by(distance_group) |>
  summarise(avg_arr_delay = mean(arr_delay, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop") |>
  arrange(distance_group)

avg_delay
# A tibble: 3 Ã 2
  distance_group          avg_arr_delay
  <chr>                           <dbl>
1 Long (1500+ miles)               2.42
2 Medium (500â1500 miles)          7.68
3 Short (<500 miles)               9.27
ggplot(avg_delay, aes(x = distance_group, y = avg_arr_delay, fill = distance_group)) +
  geom_col(show.legend = FALSE) +
  labs(x = "Flight Distance Category",
       y = "Average Arrival Delay (minutes)")
